goals.question: What is the range of values for field u and field v?

code:
```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='u', y='v')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between field u and field v?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='u', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'mean={data["u"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(x=data['u'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'median={data["u"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of field u?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='v', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['v'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'mean={data["v"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(data['v'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'median={data["v"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of field v?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.kdeplot(data=data, x="u", y="v", fill=True, cmap="Blues", levels=5, thresh=0.2, alpha=.8)
    plt.title("What is the relationship between field u and field v based on their distribution?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(data=data, ax=ax, palette="Set3")
    ax.set_title("What is the range of values for field u and field v?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
